    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>

                <p>many thanks for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> favor. <persName ref="pe0104">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Gough</persName> has sent my parcels to
                        <persName ref="pe0026">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> White</persName>. But
                    let me entreat you to send the Box of minerals shells &amp;c independent of M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> anybody that they may come to me free &amp;
                    un-rummaged. Pray send them by sea to <persName ref="pe0026">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> White</persName>: &amp; as shells are brittle
                    I beg care may be taken in package; &amp; that all may be packed very tight.
                    Thanks for all other kind intentions.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am Dear Sir <lb/>much y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">T. Pennant</persName></signed>
                <dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> June 2<hi rend="superscript">d.</hi> 1775.</dateline></closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
